# Supabase RLS & migrations

## Public catalog data
- Anonymous/authenticated clients must read jobs and company ads via **`job_offers_public`** and **`company_ads_public`** views, not base tables with contact/tax columns.
- Do not grant `SELECT` on sensitive columns of `job_offers` / `company_ads` to `anon`.

## Billing & credits
- Tables `credit_lots`, `credit_ledger`, `cv_contact_unlocks`, `stripe_credit_fulfillments`, `job_promotions`, `banner_ads`: **deny all** for `anon` and `authenticated`; mutations via `service_role` + RPCs only.
- RPCs (service_role only): `grant_credits`, `spend_credits`, `expire_due_credit_lots` — see `20260620120000_billing_cennik.sql`, `20260621152000_db_security_rpcs.sql`.
- Revoke broad DML grants on service-only tables: `20260621151000_revoke_overbroad_grants.sql`.
- Full checklist: `.cursor/rules/database-engineering.mdc`.

## User data
- `profiles`: `auth.uid() = id` for read/update own row only.
- `cv_personal_info`: sensitive columns (`email`, `phone`, `birth_date`, `gender`, street/postal) revoked from `authenticated`/`anon`; employers use Nest + `cv_contact_unlocks` (see `20260622120000_gdpr_privacy_enforcement.sql`).
- `consent_events`: users `SELECT` own rows; inserts via service_role only.

## New tables
- Default deny; add explicit policies per role.
- If a table is marketing-public, use a view with an explicit column list and document it in the migration comment.

## PWA
- Production app uses Nest API (`useApi`), not direct Supabase for business logic. RLS still matters because `NUXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` is in the bundle.
